<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-1301307" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="NSE: Turnover rises by 86.97%, other indices down 0.15%" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NSE.jpg?w=1067&amp;ssl=1 1067w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The volume of shares traded on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) on Friday rose by 86.97 per cent, just as the market indices dipped by 0.15 per cent. Specifically, investors traded 482.52 million shares valued at N4.52 billion in 3,897 deals. This was in contrast with a turnover of 258.08 million shares worth N1.68 billion, achieved in 3,640 deals on Thursday. An analysis of the activity chart indicates that Wapic Insurance was the most active, exchanging 101.09 million shares valued at N33.36 million. Unilever followed with an account of 67.87 million shares worth N848.49 million, while Zenith Bank traded 58.05 million shares, valued at N969.36 million. Access Bank traded 46.461 million shares worth N305.46 million; FBN Holdings exchanged 46.46 million shares valued at N232.88 million. However, the market capitalisation lost N20 billion or 0.15 per cent, N13.145 trillion from N13.165 trillion achieved on Thursday. Similarly, the NSE All-Share Index lost 37.13 points or 0.15 per cent, to close at 25,199.84 from 25,236.97 recorded on Thursday. CAP topped the losers’ chart, dropping by 90k to close at N17 per share. Unilever trailed with a loss of 50k to close at N12.50, while MTN Nigeria Communications was down by 50k, closing at N119 per share. Northern Nigeria Flour Mills dipped 47k to close at N3.87, while Cadbury declined by 30k to close at N7.45 per share. On the other hand, C &I Leasing led the gainers’ table, appreciating by 40k to close at N4.40 per share. BUA Cement followed with a gain of 30k to close at N38.90, while Fidson with 17k, to close at N3.70 per share. Guaranty Trust Bank added 10k to close at N24.90, Stanbic IBTC also improved by 10k, to close at N33.90 per share. Vanguard crucial indices of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) recorded a marginal growth of 0.15 per cent, after succumbing to the bears. December 7, 2018 In "News" The market capitalisation of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) on Tuesday lost N13 billion, amid profit taking embarked by investors. November 22, 2016 In "News" Activities on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) on Thursday maintained positive for the fourth straight trading session with a growth of 1.07 per cent, moving the market Year-to-Date performance into positive region. May 23, 2019 In "Business"